    "en": {
      "title": "Tamil parties' joint statement to the UN Human Rights Council",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The leaders of five Tamil parties have jointly sent a report to the United Nations Human Rights Council.",
        "The report calls for a plebiscite with international monitoring to bring about a permanent political solution for the Tamil people.",
        "Tamil People's Alliance President and Member of Parliament CV Wigneswaran, Tamil Eelam Liberation Movement Member of Parliament Selvam Adikalanathan, Tamil Eelam People's Liberation Association President and Member of Parliament Dharmalingam Siddharthan, Eelam People's Revolutionary Front President Suresh Premachandran and Tamil National Party President N. Sirikanta jointly, This report has been sent to the UN Human Rights Council.",
        "Six recommendations have been made in this report, which has been sent to the UN Human Rights Council in September. (a)"
      ],
